The paper discusses the use of adversarial learning to improve affective computing models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of multiple modalities and the analysis of affect in the wild, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories, respectively.
